					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5664948#post-3767493</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5664948/scp-3441#post-3767493</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 12 Apr 2018 20:09:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrBessile</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3856671</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think it's a shame that every single SCP is sad in some way. I know the foundation is not malevolent but you'd think they'd occasionally use the opportunity to be coldly or clinically benevolent. To me it makes sense to either allow him to continue his work (pending clones of the plant test anomalous obviously), documenting and charting all results. Or to bring him with all of his years of research on as a researcher regarding SCP-3441. Honestly the more I think about it the more actually evil it seems to steal an innocent mans life's work that is beneficial to mankind for any amount of monetary compensation let alone his knowledge of his own work.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
